Here is the cleaned up text:

Customize Your Contact Center

Grant more agents and supervisors access to voice call records and call recordings. Configure your Amazon Connect instance to seamlessly integrate with Service Cloud Voice.

To efficiently route calls, add more queues and define dynamic routing rules with Omni-Channel flows.

Voice Call Recordings

Agents and others can listen to and comment on call recordings. Ensure the right users can listen to, pause, and resume the call recordings.

Set Up Org-Wide Sharing for Voice Calls

Set up organization-wide sharing for voice calls to keep all users in sync and break down information silos.

Configure Call Transcription

Service Cloud Voice supports real-time transcription provided by Amazon Transcribe, Contact Lens for Amazon Connect, or your partner telephony provider.

Disaster Recovery for Service Cloud Voice

Use this disaster recovery plan to keep your business up and running during a Service Cloud Voice outage or planned maintenance.

Configure Single Sign-On (SSO) with Salesforce as the Identity Provider

Configure Salesforce to serve as your identity provider and follow your telephony provider's instructions for completing the setup.

Customize Call Routing

Customize call routing behavior by defining Omni-Channel flows that route calls to different queues or specific support agents.

Customize the Agent Experience
title: Enhancing Contact Center Functionality with Service Cloud
